Tacoma Block Group Mobility Index - 2014

Below is an index which estimates the mobility of residents in the various block groups of the city of Tacoma and its directly bordering areas based on the median income of the blockgroup, the portion of the block group with some sort of post-secondary degree, and the density of bicycle paths and bus stops within that block group. The former two data and polygons were acquired, dated 2014, from the US Census Bureau, while the latter were acquired from the city of Tacoma, dated 2021 and 2018 respectively. Click a block group to get a more detailed breakdown of the characteristics of that area.

Bear in mind that though the census data and polygons were for 2014, the bus and bike path data were (due to availability issues) much more recent. Considering also that this index contains only four data axes and was constructed based on individual reasoning rather than concrete research, it should be taken as suggestive rather than definitive.
